 for Energy Security and Net Zero on 6 September 2025.</p>\n\n<p>He was previously Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State at the Department for Energy Security and Net Zero from 9 July 2024 to 6 September 2025.</p>\n\n<p>He was elected as the MP for Rutherglen in October 2023.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"education\">Education</h3>\n\n<p>Michael graduated from the University of Glasgow with a degree in history and politics. He then studied for a PGDE at Glasgow.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"political-career\">Political career</h3>\n\n<p>Michael served as the Shadow Minister of State for Scotland from October 2023 to May 2024.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"career-outside-politics\">Career outside politics</h3>\n\n<p>Michael was a secondary school teacher and previously worked in the third sector on reducing offending. He ran a charity for disabled children for 15 years and is a trustee of 3 other charitable organisations.</p>\n","image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69a6d8d2a2495f2d259f13ab/s465_michael-shanks-960.png"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-09-17T14:03:33Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Michael Shanks MP","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/michael-shanks","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/minister-of-state-minister-for-energy--2","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/minister-of-state-minister-for-energy--2","base_path":"/government/ministers/minister-of-state-minister-for-energy--2","content_id":"96a50a0a-8cf7-4e14-8a29-f94b4ee0e6c9","details":{"body":"<p>The minister is responsible for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Clean Power 2030</li>\n  <li>Great British Energy</li>\n  <li>renewables and biomass</li>\n  <li>energy systems, the grid and networks</li>\n  <li>energy market reform, including <abbr title=\"Review of electricity market arrangements\">REMA</abbr> and Reformed National Pricing</li>\n  <li>energy security, resilience and preparedness</li>\n  <l